						<summary>

						<p>KŪGAḶŪR, GOBICHETTIPALAIYAM TALUK, COIMBATORE DISTRICT.</p>						

						<p>Madhyapurīśvara temple, above the entrance.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīra-Ballāḷa-dēva Pramōdūta, Tai.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records the endowment of ten <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> for a twilight lamp for God Naṭṭūrāṇḍār by Chūkkaṉ Naṭṭūraṉ, an agriculturist (<hi rend="italic">veḷḷāḷaṉ</hi>) of Kūvalūr in Kāñchikkūval-nāḍu. The amount was deposited with Āvuḍaiyār Nāyakanambiyār of <hi rend="italic">Bhāradvāja-gōtra,</hi> a śivabrahmaṇa, having <hi rend="italic">kāṇi</hi> of the temple. </p>						

						</summary>
